Adjust rack to top position (top and middle for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @delicata squash{1} lengthwise; scoop out and discard seeds with a #spoon{}. Cut squash crosswise into ¾-inch-thick slices. Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%oz}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Roughly chop @pecans{1/2%oz}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, add @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Microwave until completely melted, ~{45-60%seconds}.

Toss squash and Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with melted butter, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast on top rack, flipping veggies halfway through, until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. (For 4, divide between 2 sheets; roast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through.)

While veggies roast, in a second small microwave-safe bowl, combine @maple syrup{2%tbsp}, @honey{2%tsp}, @chipotle powder{1/8%tsp} (¼ tsp for 4 servings—be sure to measure; >we sent more), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Microwave for ~{20%seconds}, then set aside.

Trim and mince @scallions{2}(trimmed and minced). Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and minced).

In a third #small bowl{}, combine scallions, garlic, half the lemon zest (all for 4 servings), @olive oil{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4), and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Pat @bavette steak{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large #stainless steel pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until browned on one side, ~{4-6%minutes}. Flip steak; reduce heat to medium low and cook for ~{2%minutes} more.

Add @butter{4%tbsp} (6 TBSP for 4 servings) and cook until foamy. Tilt pan slightly towards the handle and spoon melted butter over steak, repeating often, until steak reaches desired doneness, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Transfer steak to a #cutting board{}. Let rest for ~{5%minutes}.

While steak cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @ricotta cheese{4%oz}, @crème fraîche{4%tbsp}, a squeeze of lemon juice (two squeezes for 4 servings), @olive oil{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4), and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} until light and fluffy. Taste and season with more salt and pepper if desired.

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Microwave chipotle syrup for ~{15%seconds}.

Spread whipped ricotta on one side of each #plate{}. Pile roasted veggies over top; drizzle with as much chipotle syrup as you like. Garnish with pecans. Place steak next to veggies; top with 1 TBSP pan juices (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and gremolata. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.